 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Flight Advisor SimpleCharters Portsmouth, VA Remote Full-time Employer actively reviewed job 4 days ago Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Join a fast-growing company that is transforming its industry! SimpleCharters is a private jet charter aviation company making it easier than ever to book a private Jet...in just 3 simple clicks. 
 We are looking for dynamic Flight Advisors to join our Charter Operations Team. You will be the face of the company for our clients, guiding them from initial inquiry to wheels up to touchdown. You will need to be well organized to manage a large volume of flights with clients, and when a client has a special need or request, you will go the extra mile to exceed their expectations. Along the way, you will be working with our product and engineering teams providing guidance on how best to improve our software for efficiency and scalability. 
 Job Description: 
 Manage our proprietary data set on the best charter operators and charter aircraft in the industry 
Work hand-in-hand with team members to deliver an exceptional flight experience 
Manage contracts with operators, and hold them accountable to delivering an exceptional experience for our clients 
As needed and especially in recovery situations, source quotes and contracts from operators to fulfill client itineraries 
Be able to take the lead in recovery operations as well as be able to support team members as needed 
Develop trust and rapport with charter operator staff 
Help guide our product and engineering teams on how to improve efficiency, accuracy and overall customer experience 
When everything is going well, be the voice in the room that asks the tough questions for how to prepare for when it inevitably goes wrong 
Ensure client trips are on schedule by flight following the repo and live legs. Communicate in with the client in real time of any unexpected changes 
 Our ideal candidate: 
 Experience in general aviation – ideally working in charter and/or scheduling-logistics 
A phenomenal communicator, both verbally and in writing 
Self-directed and detail oriented, with a can and will do attitude 
Excited to explore how AI, machine learning and automation can help the operations team be more efficient 
Works well in a team environment, but when needed can take a leadership role 
Has the ability to remain calm and focus their efforts during high stress situations and to prioritize tasks accordingly 
Intellectually curious, with a demonstrated commitment to continuous growth 
Looking to join a growing company with a vibrant, entrepreneurial culture, dedicated to being the top provider in the private jet charter space 
 Ideally looking for candidates w/ 2+ years of charter aviation experience 
 Broker experience desired 
Logistics/scheduling experience 
Experience with outsourcing and trip recoveries SimpleCharters 30+ days ago original job If you require alternative methods of application or screening, you must approach the employer directly to request this as Indeed is not responsible for the employer's application process. Report job Apply Now Apply Now Save this job Save this job Jobs at SimpleCharters in Portsmouth, VA Company Info Follow Get job updates from SimpleCharters Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
 
